quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  33,7,"And when We made a covenant with the prophets and with you (Muhammad), and with Noah and Abraham and Moses and Jesus, son of Mary, We made with them a strong (solemn) covenant"
  33,8,"That He may question the Custodians of Truth about the truth (or the Loyal about loyalty), and He has prepared for the unfaithful a painful doom"
  33,9,"O you who believe! Call to mind the favour of Allah to you when there came down upon you hosts, so We sent against them a strong wind and hosts that you saw not, and Allah is Seer what you do"
  33,10,"When they came upon you from above you and from below you, and when the eyes turned dull, and the heart rose up to the throats, and you began to think vain thoughts of Allah"
  33,11,There the believers were sorely tried and they were shaken with severe shaking
  33,12,"And when the hypocrites and those in whose heart was a disease began to say, \"Allah and His Apostle did not promise us nothing but delusion"
  33,13,"And when a party of them said, \"O people of Yathrib! there is no place to stand for you (here), therefore go back\"; and a party of them asked permission of the Prophet, saying. \"Surely our houses are exposed\"; and they were not exposed"
  33,14,"And if the enemy had entered upon them from the outlying parts of it, and they had been exhorted to treachery, they would certainly have done it, and they would have hesitated but little"
  33,15,"And certainly they had made a covenant with Allah before, that they would not turn their backs; and AllahÂ´s covenant shall be answered for"